    "title": "Getting Started",
    "description": "Get started with Memokit in minutes",
    "content": "# Getting Started\n\nWelcome to Memokit! This guide will help you get up and running quickly.\n\n## Overview\n\nGetting started with Memokit involves three simple steps:\n\n1. **Create an account** - Sign up at [console.memokit.dev](https://console.memokit.dev)\n2. **Get your API key** - Generate an API key from the console\n3. **Make your first API call** - Start storing and searching memories\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- A Memokit account\n- An API key (starts with `mk_`)\n- Any HTTP client (curl, Postman, or your favorite programming language)\n\n## Quick Links\n\n- [Quickstart Guide](/docs/getting-started/quickstart) - Step-by-step tutorial\n- [Authentication](/docs/getting-started/authentication) - API key management\n- [API Reference](/docs/api-reference) - Full API documentation\n\n## Base URL\n\nAll API requests should be made to:\n\n```\nhttps://api.memokit.dev\n```\n\n## Support\n\nIf you need help:\n\n- Check the [API Reference](/docs/api-reference) for detailed documentation\n- Review [Best Practices](/docs/guides/best-practices) for optimization tips\n- Contact support at support@memokit.dev",
